JOHANNESBURG - Cricket South Africa (CSA) confirmed on Tuesday that the T20 Global League has been postponed. The event was scheduled to begin on November 3. READ: Pollard to lead Bloem City Blazers in T20 Global League The postponement comes in the wake of the resignation of former CSA CEO Haroon Lorgat in September. Interim CSA CEO Thabang Moroe said that CSA would be facing a $25 million (R342 million) loss for the staging of the tournament. African News Agency